feed.title: IonQ Expands in EU With Slovakia’s First National Quantum Communication Network
feed.summary: IonQ, through its subsidiary ID Quantique, has deployed Slovakia's first national quantum communication network in partnership with the Institute of Physics, Slovak Academy of Sciences. The network will connect key institutions in Bratislava, reinforcing Slovakia's commitment to strategic research and cybersecurity, and builds on IonQ's expanding presence in Europe.

feed.title: Geneva & Bratislava: IonQ Expands European Quantum Network Reach

This network uses a hybrid architecture of Quantum Key Distribution (QKD) and post-quantum cryptography to enhance cybersecurity for critical institutions, contributing to the broader European Quantum Communication Infrastructure (EuroQCI) initiative. This deployment expands IonQ's presence in Europe, building on its Geneva Quantum Network and other initiatives to advance quantum technology across the continent.
